# Normalize train data
train_datay = Y_train
min_ytrain = np.min(train_datay, axis=0)
max_ytrain = np.max(train_datay, axis=0)
nytrain = (train_datay - min_ytrain) / (max_ytrain - min_ytrain)

# Normalize test data using the same min and max values from the train data
test_datay = Y_test
nytest = (test_datay - min_ytrain) / (max_ytrain - min_ytrain)
nytest

def bulid_clf(ginp):
    u_model= keras.Sequential([
        keras.layers.Dense(ginp, input_shape=(1024,), activation='sigmoid'),
        keras.layers.Dense(50, activation='sigmoid'),
        keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='sigmoid')
        ])



    u_model.compile(optimizer='adam',
                loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
                metrics=['accuracy'])

    return u_model
